  "prompt": "How does AdMob know if your app violates their ToS?",
  "response": "AdMob employs several methods to determine if an app violates their Terms of Service (ToS). Here's an overview of the main strategies AdMob uses:\n\n1. **Automated Systems and Algorithms:** AdMob uses automated systems and algorithms that scan and analyze apps to detect suspicious patterns. These algorithms are designed to identify common violations, such as inappropriate content, click fraud, or misleading practices.\n\n2. **Manual Reviews:** AdMob also has teams of reviewers who manually inspect apps and their associated content. These reviewers are trained to spot violations that automated systems might miss, ensuring a thorough assessment of apps.\n\n3. **User Reports:** AdMob allows users and developers to report apps that may be violating their ToS. These reports are reviewed by AdMob's team, and appropriate action is taken if the app is found to be in violation.\n\n4. **Collaboration with Other Google Services:** AdMob collaborates with other Google services, such as Google Play, to identify apps that violate policies across the platform. If an app is flagged on Google Play for violating its policies, this information can be shared with AdMob for further investigation.\n\n5. **Behavioral Analysis:** AdMob monitors how users interact with ads within the app. Unusual patterns, such as a high number of invalid clicks or other fraudulent activities, can trigger an investigation.\n\n6. **Policy Updates and Notifications:** AdMob regularly updates its policies and terms of service. Developers are required to stay informed and comply with these updates. AdMob provides notifications and resources to help developers understand the guidelines and ensure compliance.\n\n7. **Machine Learning:** Advanced machine learning techniques are employed to improve the detection of violations over time. These systems learn from past violations and continuously evolve to identify new types of non-compliant behavior.\n\nIf an app is found to be in violation of AdMob's ToS, the developer may receive warnings, face temporary suspensions, or have their account terminated, depending on the severity of the violation. Developers are encouraged to review AdMob's policies regularly and ensure their apps comply to avoid any negative consequences.",
